## Front-End Requirements (Angular)
1. Create interfaces and services to interact with back-end APIs [done]
2. At least 4 (click) events that trigger API requests [done]
3. At least 4 form controls using [(ngModel)] (FormsModule) [done]
4. Apply basic CSS styling to components 
5. Set up the Routing module with at least 3 named routes and navigation between pages [done]
6. Use @for to loop over data and @if for conditional rendering (Angular 17+; legacy *ngFor/*ngIf accepted on older versions)
7. JWT authentication: HTTP interceptor, login page, logout functionality
8. At least 1 Angular Service using HttpClient for all API communication
9. Handle API errors gracefully (e.g., display error messages to the user on failed requests)

---

## Back-end Requirements (Django + DRF)
1. Define at least 4 models [done]
2. Optionally, create 1 custom model manager [done]
3. Include at least 2 ForeignKey relationships between models [done]
4. Serializers:
  At least 2 from serializers.Serializer [done]
  At least 2 from serializers.ModelSerializer [done]
5. Views:
  At least 2 Function-Based Views (FBV) using DRF decorators [done]
  At least 2 Class-Based Views (CBV) using APIView [done]
6. Token-based authentication with login and logout endpoints [done]
7. When creating objects, link them to the authenticated user (e.g., request.user)
8. Configure CORS (django-cors-headers) to allow requests from the Angular dev server

